  "text": "Pod security context validation in Kubernetes is implemented across two main components:\n\n1. **Admission Control Layer**: The PodSecurity admission controller (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/) implements pod security standards validation through policy checks that enforce restricted and baseline policies.\n\n2. **Core Validation**: The kubernetes API validation layer (pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go) provides field-level validation for security context attributes.\n\n**RunAsNonRoot Enforcement** is validated in check_runAsNonRoot.go which implements the CheckRunAsNonRoot() function and its corresponding runAsNonRoot_1_0() check function. This enforces the restricted policy level requirement that pods must set securityContext.runAsNonRoot=true either at the pod or container level.\n\n**Privileged Container Check** is implemented in check_privileged.go through the CheckPrivileged() function and privileged_1_0() check function. This baseline policy forbids setting securityContext.privileged=true on any container within a pod.\n\n**Capabilities Validation** is split into two levels:\n- Baseline level: check_capabilities_baseline.go implements CheckCapabilitiesBaseline() which allows only default capabilities (AUDIT_WRITE, CHOWN, DAC_OVERRIDE, FOWNER, FSETID, KILL, MKNOD, NET_BIND_SERVICE, SETFCAP, SETGID, SETPCAP, SETUID, SYS_CHROOT) to be added via securityContext.capabilities.add.\n- Restricted level: check_capabilities_restricted.go implements CheckCapabilitiesRestricted() which requires containers to drop ALL capabilities and only allows NET_BIND_SERVICE to be added.\n\n**SeccompProfile Enforcement** is split into two versions:\n- Baseline level: check_seccompProfile_baseline.go implements CheckSeccompBaseline() with version-specific checks (seccompProfileBaseline_1_0 for annotation-based validation and seccompProfileBaseline_1_19 for field-based validation). Baseline allows runtime/default, docker/default, or localhost profiles.\n- Restricted level: check_seccompProfile_restricted.go implements CheckSeccompProfileRestricted() which requires a seccomp profile to be set and only allows RuntimeDefault or Localhost types.\n\n**Core API Validation** in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go implements:\n- ValidateSecurityContext(): validates SecurityContext fields including privileged flag and capabilities restrictions\n- validateSeccompProfileField(): validates seccomp profile configuration\n- validatePodSpecSecurityContext(): validates pod-level security context including seccomp profiles\n\nThese validation layers work together to enforce Kubernetes Pod Security Standards through the admission controller plugin (plugin/pkg/admission/security/podsecurity/admission.go) which delegates to the upstream pod-security-admission library (staging/src/k8s.io/pod-security-admission/) for policy evaluation and enforcement."
}

